09/05/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Paddy Ashdown launched a Defence Reform Commission in BiH on Thursday (8 May). The panel will include top international and BiH representatives and will be asked to come up with a consensus on the legal requirements to reform the country's defence structures, as well as prepare legislation in line with modern European practices. Ashdown wants drafts and recommendations by the end of September. (OHR Sources, BH Radio 1, BBC, RTRS, PBS BiH - 08/05/03)
